hypothesis.value:
There are two principal research objectives;
(1) Can we replicate and extend key outcomes from a study of joint cognition (the AABB study), generalising this to asymmetric production schedules (AAB / ABB)
(2) If participants are assigned to outgroups through a minimal-group-paradigm MGP intervention, does this affect their collaborative stance and production choices in the joint cognition paradigm?

